The paper deals with finding vertex subsets in graphs that satisfy certain properties, which is a topic in algorithmic graph theory. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the paper explores the (parameterized) complexity of finding secluded vertex subsets for a variety of properties, which could fall under the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The paper also mentions minimizing separators, feedback vertex sets, F-free vertex deletion sets, dominating sets, and maximizing independent sets, which are all topics in graph theory and could place the paper in the cs.GT (Graph Theory) sub-category. The focus on limiting the "exposure" of the solution to the rest of the graph suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions exploring the influence of constraints on the complexity of finding secluded vertex subsets, which could fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
